<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post220105"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Boanerges</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">The Forehead(tm) <br> Moderator</font><br>
	<img src="avatar.php?userid=1399&dateline=1073944307" border="0" alt=""><p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Feb 2000<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 2370</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"><img src="../ubb/icons/icon2.gif" alt="Arrow" border="0"> <b>Guild Summit: SOE trying to save EQ?</b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">So last night we're raiding VZ in Tactics when a GM Admin names Saiphos shows up. This guy is nothing like the GMs I've seen of late. The guy was... well, pleasant to be around. We cracked jokes and he cracked right back. It was very cool.<br />
<br />
Pity we hadn't petitioned for anything.<br />
<br />
He was there to talk to our GL about attending this summit. This was the email sent to him before Saiphos showed up.<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>From: Events<br />
Date: Tuesday, May 25, 2004 4:02 PM<br />
To: *email removed*<br />
Subject: Guild Summit Invitation from John Smedley<br />
<br />
Dear *EQ name*,<br />
<br />
Over the years I have had been fortunate enough to have had the<br />
opportunity to speak or e-mail with many of the high-end EverQuest<br />
guilds. I firmly believe that EverQuest's success in the MMO world is<br />
built upon the strong foundation of a loyal player-base. But with<br />
development cycles, trade-shows, Fan Faires, etc., we rarely get the<br />
opportunity to talk in a smaller venue. I thought it would be a great<br />
opportunity to take advantage of some of the great San Diego weather and<br />
invite you to visit SOE for a guild summit from June 4th-6th.<br />
<br />
I'd like to get the leaders of the top guilds in EverQuest, past and<br />
present, bring them to San Diego, put you up in a hotel, and give you an<br />
opportunity to give us direct feedback regarding EverQuest and your<br />
experiences with it.<br />
<br />
Along with a venue for personal feedback, we will give you a<br />
personalized tour of the SOE San Diego development studios, have a<br />
barbecue lunch with EverQuest developers, and even take you to a San<br />
Diego Padres game at our new ballpark, Petco Park (first beer's on me!).<br />
I'll buy dinner on Saturday night to be sure the weekend ends on a good<br />
note.<br />
<br />
Vannoth and Brenlo will be your hosts for the event (so there will be<br />
fun to be had at all times).<br />
<br />
Due to logistical constraints, we can only extend this invitation to one<br />
person per invited guild; if you are unable to attend, you may appoint<br />
one of your officers to attend in your place. However, please note that<br />
this invitation is open to people in the contiguous 48 US States, so if<br />
you are international, please appoint an officer who lives in the 48<br />
states to attend.<br />
<br />
Please respond to this email within 48 hours of receipt to confirm that<br />
you or one of your officers will be in attendance. If you would please<br />
respond with:<br />
<br />
The name of the person attending<br />
Their contact information (Email, Phone, etc)<br />
Their physical address (so we can book airfare)<br />
Their T-shirt size<br />
<br />
We will be booking flights for the morning/afternoon of Friday, June 4th<br />
to give us plenty of time to check in to the hotel and attend the Padres<br />
game at 7:05 PST. (Return flights will be scheduled for Sunday, June<br />
6th.)<br />
<br />
If you have any questions, you may call *edited out*.<br />
<br />
This should prove to be a great time for everyone. Hope to see you in<br />
San Diego!<br />
<br />
Sincerely,<br />
John Smedley<br />
President<br />
Sony Online Entertainment<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
To sum it up, they're giving him and the leaders of the top guilds in EQ an all expense paid trip to San Diego. I think AL leaving was a major warning sign.<br />
<br />
Of course our good pal Woody over at GU Comics had some harsh things to say too before all this<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>SOE's rapid push for this next expansion is little more than a money grab attempt by the corporate big whigs before the well runs dry. In other words, Smedley and his peers has his hand buried elbow deep in our pockets digging for every scrap of our cash that they can get. Unlike the Devs and CS staff, these people in the company echelon are not concerned with the quality of the game, or the feelings of the players and fans. Their only interest is in the financial gain. Smedley has said as much himself.<br />
<br />
In my opinion EQ is not ready for another expansion. I agree with one of my SOE contacts that OoW should not be released until Q4, and the dev staff should be allowed to work on EQ throughout the summer to shore up the system, correct bugs, work with graphics, optimization, etc.<br />
<br />
Like I said, it's not the dev staff or cs team that are to blame for the state of EQ right now. The entire burden rests on the shoulders of the money grubbers. And, the only way we're going to effect change within the game is if we affect the bottom line. What I'm saying to you is...<br />
<br />
Don't purchase Omens of War.<br />
<br />
We will only convince Smedley and his ilk to give the devs the go ahead to change the game, if we absolutely REFUSE to buy any more trash exansions in the HOPES that we'll actually get our money's worth.<br />
<br />
We have to put our proverbial foot down, force them to extract their fingers from our wallets, and engender an atmosphere of "no more money without change".<br />
<br />
For most of us, EQ is no longer fun. It's no longer the game we fell in love with. I for one want that game back. I want the devs to have their way with the game. Looking at the other popular MMOG's on the market, I want the devs to be allowed to alter the game to make it fun again. And, they want to. They've been begging to. But, the higher ups aren't listening.<br />
<br />
This, I guess, is my initial "call to arms". This community has to rally the rest of the EQ collective to make a stand. Let's put our credit cards away. Let's show them by not paying for the game, that we're unwilling to be force fed quick-fire expansions like Omens ever again. <hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
And after...<br />
<br />
<blockquote><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><hr>15 Hours and a call from Smedley later...<br />
<br />
<br />
I initially received an email from Alan "Brenlo" Crosby, getting a feeler for the situation and getting my phone number.<br />
<br />
Alan then called to briefly talk to me, and let me know that Mr. Smedley would like to talk to me about a few things. I was also invited out to a "Guild Summit" coming up next Friday that is designed to have some of the guild and community leaders come out and help SOE get the game back on track by voicing their concerns.<br />
<br />
Shortly after Brenlo and I got off the phone Smedley called to talk to me about the game in general, my concerns, Omens of War, etc. I would seem to me that SOE has gotten their wake up call. They are ready to take a step back and try to nail down the problems with the game.<br />
<br />
Chief among the info he gave me is that Omens is going to be pushed back 6 weeks, and the time between now and then will be used to correct the issues in the game. Not stuff like class balance etc, but fixing bugs etc.<hr></blockquote><br />
<br />
An interesting turn of events to say the least.<br />
<br />
Do you think EQ can be saved?</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=289957" target="_blank">Boanerges Thundercry</a><br />
