<table bgcolor="#FFFFFF" width="95%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tr><td width="10"><img width="10" height="1" src="images/space.gif" alt=""></td><td width="100%"><!-- spacer -->

<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" bgcolor=""  width="95%" align="center"><tr><td>
<table cellpadding="4" cellspacing="1" border="0"  width="100%">
<tr>
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="175" valign="top" nowrap>
	<a name="post220133"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Velisaris</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Keeper of the TPS reports</font><br>
	<img src="avatar.php?userid=5218&dateline=1031257511" border="0" alt=""><p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Nov 2001<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 1316</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#F7F7F7" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Here's the thing...<br />
<br />
SOE has, what, two fan fairs a year?  What makes anyone think that a "special" meeting with guild leaders of high end guilds is going to accomplish more than what could be accomplished by events that are open to all types of players?  I remember the last "secrect" meeting they had with representatives of the EQ community...and I remember that from all reports, it was nothing more than an exhibition to promote the next expansion/EQ2.<br />
<br />
A summit with only the "uber" guilds represented means absolutely squat to the average EQ player.  Why bother having fan fairs for everyone if only a select few get to voice their opinions in meetings that are invitation only?  I think this is another round of lip service from Smed and SOE to try and retain as many players as they can before the next MMORPG competitor steps up to the plate to take a swing and try to dethrone EQ.<br />
<br />
A move like this serves one purpose and one purpose only...it sends a message to the non-uber, casual, single-account players (you know, the players that actually make up the majority of EQ's playerbase) that says "Screw off, we don't care what you think."</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=348594" target="_blank">Exarch Velisaris Groovenhymer</a><br />
Erudite Archon of Quellious (retired)<br />
Maelin Starpyre server<br />
--------------------------------------<br />
"I came...I saw...I got bored and cancelled my account."</font></p></p>
	<p></p>
