	<a name="post220134"></a>
	
	<font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial"><b>Araon</b></font><br>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</font><br>
	<p>
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">Registered: Oct 2003<br>
	Location: <br>
	Posts: 18</font></td>
	
	<td bgcolor="#DEDFDF" width="100%" valign="top">
	<font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial"> <b></b></font>
	<p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">Don't get me wrong, I like the fact they are listening to the player base.  And the high end guilds should have a voice - but they are not the be all and end all of the game.  How are GoD focussed raiding guilds going to communicate the concerns and frustrations of non-raiders who are never going to see the elemental planes much less Uqua?<br />
<br />
I just don't understand why they need to spend all that money on plane tickets and hotel rooms when that wonderful invention known as the "Internet" means you can communicate equally well using a computer.<br />
<br />
SoE is a for-profit corporation - every dime spent on airfare and hotels has to come from somewhere.  Why not spend it on actual programming and game design rather than a massive exercise in public relations?</font></p>
	
	<p><p><font size="2" face="Verdana, Arial">__________________<br>
Araon Trueheart<br />
Cleric of 65 Heals and Buffs<br />
Torv</font></p></p>
